-- Manchester City Increases Bid for Milner to $37 Million: Soccer Roundup
-- Danielle Rossingh
-- 2010-07-23T09:49:57Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-23/manchester-city-increases-bid-for-milner-to-37-million-soccer-roundup.html

          
          
             The following is a roundup of soccer
stories from U.K. newspapers, with clickable links to the Web.  
 City Raise Milner Bid  
 Manchester City has increased its offer for Aston Villa
player  James Milner  to 24 million pounds ($37 million), the
 Guardian  reported. Although Villa is asking 30 million pounds
for the England international, negotiations are expected to
continue, the paper said.  
 Mascherano Demands Inter Move  
 Javier Mascherano  will demand a move to Inter Milan from
Liverpool, the  Daily Mail  reported. Inter is willing to pay 20
million pounds for the Argentina captain, while Liverpool is
asking for 30 million pounds, the paper said.  
 United Boosts Vidic Offer  
 Manchester United has made  Nemanja Vidic  a new offer that
would make the defender one of the highest earnings players at
the club, the  Guardian  said.  
 Campbell Stays Put  
 Defender  Sol Campbell  has decided to stay at Arsenal for
another year, the  Sun  said. The player had received offers to
play for Newcastle, Celtic and Middlesbrough.  
 Sven to Fulham?  
 Former England manager Sven-Goran Eriksson is in the
running to take over the managerial job at Fulham after  Martin Jol  decided to stay at Ajax, the  Guardian  said.  
